To understand Foucault, you need to understand his background.
Despite his fervor against the “bourgeois,” he had a privileged upper-class upbringing in France, and descended from a long-time of surgeons.
He suffered from depression and self-mutilation, largely stemming from his repressed sexuality and interest in sadomasochism.
He was sent to a psychiatrist, which started his fascination with medicine, knowledge, and power.
